# E-commerce Data Analysis with Python & SQL

Advanced data analysis of Brazilian e-commerce operations using SQL queries and Python visualizations.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.x
- MySQL
- Libraries: Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn, mysql-connector-python

## Key Features

### Data Analysis Pipeline
- Automated CSV to MySQL database ingestion
- Dynamic table creation with appropriate data types
- Null value handling and data cleaning
- Batch processing of multiple CSV files

### Business Intelligence
- Geographic customer distribution analysis
- Sales trends and YoY growth metrics
- Product category performance evaluation
- Customer retention analysis

### Visualization
- Interactive charts for sales trends
- Customer distribution maps
- Product performance visualizations
- Payment pattern analysis

## Setup and Usage

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/SAMUR274/PYTHON-SQL-DataAnalysis_Project.git

# Install dependencies
pip install pandas matplotlib seaborn mysql-connector-python
```

Configure database connection:
```python
db = mysql.connector.connect(
    host="localhost",
    username="root",
    password="your_password",
    database="ecommerce"
)
```

## Project Structure
```
├── data_import.py      # Database setup and data ingestion
├── analysis_queries.py # SQL queries for business insights
└── README.md          # Documentation
```

## Analysis Categories

### Basic Queries
- Customer location analysis
- Order volume tracking (2017)
- Category-wise sales metrics
- Installation payment analysis

### Advanced Analytics
- Moving averages for order values
- Customer retention rates
- Top customer identification
- YoY growth calculations

## Key Findings
- 45,101 orders placed in 2017
- 99.99% orders used installment payments
- -0.106 price-purchase correlation
- 20% YoY growth in 2018

